gomodel:SYNGO_3954  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Zhong et.al. use overexpression of GFP-tagged proteins to test the subcellular localization of PKA subunits in hippocampal slice cultures. They observe that PKA R1a-GFP is present in dendrites, including dendritic spines (Figure 2C, D).\nIt is also observed that PKA R1a-GFP expression is somewhat reduced in the axon. This indicates that this experiment has at least some specificity, but the evidence is not very strong.. Experimental description: Cultured hippocampal slices were prepared (Stoppini et al., 1991\n) from P6-7 rats or mice in accordance with the animal care and use guidelines of Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory and Janelia Farm Research Institute. Experiments were performed at 8-16 days in vitro." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2020-07-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3954" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

